ROB16745 | Dynamic Optimization | https://enr-apps.as.cmu.edu/open/SOC/SOCServlet/courseDetails?COURSE=16745&SEMESTER=S17 | instructors:Atkeson, Christopher description:This course surveys the use of optimization (especially optimal  control) to design behavior.  We will explore ways to represent  policies including hand-designed parametric functions, basis  functions, tables, and trajectory libraries. We will also explore  algorithms to create policies including parameter optimization and  trajectory optimization (first and second order gradient methods,  sequential quadratic programming, random search methods, evolutionary  algorithms, etc.).  We will discuss how to handle the discrepancy  between models used to create policies and the actual system being  controlled (evaluation and robustness issues). The course will combine  lectures, student-presented material, and projects. The goal of this  course will be to help participants find the most effective methods  for their problems.
